n","e":"khaṣāṣatun"},{"b":"36.","h":"54.65","c":"وَمَنْ","d":"waman","e":"waman"},{"b":"37.4","h":"56.21","c":"يُوقَ","d":"yūqa","e":"yūqa"},{"b":"38","h":"57.3","c":"شُحَّ","d":"shuḥḥa","e":"shuḥḥa"},{"b":"38.","h":"58.33","c":"نَفْسِهِ","d":"nafsihi","e":"nafsihi"},{"b":"39.7","h":"60.02","c":"فَأُولَئِكَ","d":"fa-ulāika","e":"fa-ulāika"},{"b":"42.7","h":"63.31","c":"هُمُ","d":"humu","e":"humu"},{"b":"43.2","h":"64.12","c":"الْمُفْلِحُونَ","d":"l-muf'liḥūna","e":"l-muf'liḥūna"}],"a":{"g":"And [also for] those who were settled in al-Madinah and [adopted] the faith before them. They love those who emigrated to them and find not any want in their breasts of what the emigrants were given but give [them] preference over themselves, even though they are in privation. And whoever is protected from the stinginess of his soul - it is those who will be the successful.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                ومنها أن يكون مؤثراً ما أحبه الله تعالى على ما يحبه في ظاهره وباطنه فيلزم مشاق العمل ويجتنب إتباع الهوى ويعرض عنه دعة الكسل، ولا يزال مواظباً على طاعة الله ومتقرباً إليه بالنوافل وطالباً عنده مزايا الدرجات كما يطلب المحب مزيد القرب في قلب محبوبه، وقد وصف الله تعالى المحبين بالإيثار فقال: \" يحبون من هاجر إليهم ولا يجدون في صدورهم حاجة مما أوتوا ويؤثرون على أنفسهم ولو كان بهم خصاصة \" ومن بقي مستقراً على متابعة الهوى فمحبوبه ما يهواه، بل يترك المحب هوى نفسه كما قيل: |أريد وصاله   | |فأترك ما   | |ويريد هجري   | |أريد لمـا  | |             | |يريد       | بل الحب إذا غلب قمع الهوى فلم يبق له تنعم بغير المحبوب.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                And from them is that he prefers [yu'thiru] what God the Exalted loves over what he himself loves, in his outward [zahir] and inward [batin]. Thus, he adheres to the hardships of striving [masha'iq al-'amal] and avoids following caprice [hawa], and turns away from the comfort of indolence. He remains constant in obedience to God [ta'at Allah] and draws near to Him through supererogatory acts [nawafil], seeking with Him the distinctions of ranks [darajat], just as the lover seeks increased nearness in the heart [qalb] of his beloved. And God the Exalted has described the lovers with preferring [ithar], saying: \"They love those who emigrated to them and find in their breasts no need for what they have been given, but prefer [yu'thiruna] them over themselves, even though poverty is their lot.\"\n\nAnd whoever remains settled upon following caprice [hawa], then his beloved is what he desires [yahwa]. Rather, the lover abandons the caprice [hawa] of his soul [nafs], as it is said:\n\"I desire union with him, so I abandon what I desire,\nAnd he desires my separation, so I desire what he desires.\"\n\nIndeed, when love [hubb] overcomes, it subdues caprice [hawa], so that no enjoyment remains for it except through the Beloved.\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"10":{"w":[{"b":"0.15","h":"1.1","c":"وَالَّذِينَ","d":"wa-alladhīna","e":"wa-alladhīna"},{"b":"1.3","h":"2.98","c":"جَاءُو","d":"jāū","e":"jāū"},{"b":"4.3","h":"5.59","c":"مِنْ","d":"min","e":"min"},{"b":"5.4","h":"6.58","c":"بَعْدِهِمْ","d":"baʿdihim","e":"baʿdihim"},{"b":"6.4","h":"8.17","c":"يَقُولُونَ","d":"yaqūlūna","e":"yaqūlūna"},{"b":"7.7","h":"10.23","c":"رَبَّنَا","d":"rabbanā","e":"rabbanā"},{"b":"8.5","h":"11.48","c":"اغْفِرْ","d":"igh'fir","e":"igh'fir"},{"b":"9.3","h":"12.33","c":"لَنَا","d":"lanā","e":"lanā"},{"b":"10","h":"13.58","c":"وَلِإِخْوَانِنَا","d":"wali-ikh'wāninā","e":"wali-ikh'wāninā"},{"b":"11.6","h":"16.2","c":"الَّذِينَ","d":"alladhīna","e":"